What version of Oracle?  In 12.2 or later, you can

    select name, sum( to_number( text default 0 on conversion error ))
      from your_table
     group by name;

In earlier versions, I generally prefer something like

    create or replace function safe_to_number( p_str in varchar2 )
      return number
    is
      l_ret number;
    begin
      l_ret := to_number( p_str );
      return l_ret;
    exception
      when others then
        return null;
    end;
    
    select name, safe_to_number( text )
      from your_table
     group by name

Regular expression based solutions that look for numbers can work but they tend to get complicated quickly.  &quot;1.00&quot; may be a number (assuming the decimal separator is the period), &quot;1.00.00&quot; is not, &quot;-100&quot; is a number &quot;1-00&quot; is not, etc.  You can generally play with the regular expression for a while so that it works with whatever data you have but it&#39;s hard to be confident that you&#39;ve covered every case.  If you decide that you want to handle special cases differently (i.e. you have Indian users that enter one hundred thousand as 1,00,000) then you can update the function to iterate through a series of format masks before giving up on the conversion.

I believe you&#39;ll have to work with the `HttpWebRequest` class to do it this.

Something like this:

    HttpWebrequest request = _httpClient.Request(url, contentType);
    
    request.AllowWriteStreamBuffering = false;
    
    using( var stream = await request.GetRequestStreamAsync().ConfigureAwait(false))
    {
